  "summary": "The US captured Venezuelan President Maduro on January 3, 2026, prompting widespread international condemnation including from US allies like France and the UN Secretary General. Historical precedents are strong: the UNGA condemned both the US invasion of Panama (1989, resolution within 9 days) and Grenada (1983, resolution within 8 days) in very analogous situations. However, 8 days have passed with no Security Council resolution vote and no UNGA draft resolution, which is slower than the Panama/Grenada precedents where SC votes occurred within 3 days. The Iraq 2003 counter-precedent shows that even massive opposition doesn't guarantee UNGA action. The UNGA may be in January recess, adding procedural friction, and Trump-era political dynamics may discourage formal action. With 20 days remaining, there's still time, but the absence of any formal process starting is a meaningful negative signal.",
